The Three Kingdoms are now at Peace; and we have a Parliament that is no Friend to the Faction. The King is Possest of a Considerable Guard, which his Royal Father wanted. The Militia is in safe Hands. His Majesty is likewise possest


of his Regal Power, and Revenue: And his Capital City firm in its Obedience: To all which may be added, that although divers Particulars are as Wealthy as Pillage, and Pardon, can make them; Yet They want a Common Stock to carry on a Common Cause. The Thimbles, and the Bedkins fail; and the Comfortable In-comes of Ex. Coll. p 84. 
